r><dc:description><abstract xmlns="" original="y" xml:lang="eng">
<ce:para>We study the structure of the nilpotent commutator N <inf>B</inf> of a nilpotent matrix B. We show that N <inf>B</inf> intersects all nilpotent orbits for conjugation if and only if B is a square-zero matrix. We describe nonempty intersections of N <inf>B</inf> with nilpotent orbits in the case the n × n matrix B has rank n - 2. Moreover, we give some results concerning the inverse image of the map taking B to the maximal nilpotent orbit intersecting N <inf>B</inf>. © 2012 Copyright Taylor and Francis Group, LLC.</ce:para>
